  <description>from a 2D image.</description>
  <command interpreter="bash">
    show_RGB_image.sh $input $red $green $blue
  </command>
  <inputs>
   <param format="tiff" name="input" type="data" label="2D images" />
    <param name="red" type="integer" value="1" label="Red channel index" />
    <param name="green" type="integer" value="2" label="Green channel index" />
    <param name="blue" type="integer" value="3" label="Blue channel index" />
  </inputs>
  <stdio>
    <exit_code range="2" level="fatal" description="Output image not present" />
  </stdio>
  <outputs>
    <data format="png" name="output" from_work_dir="output.png"/>
  </outputs>
<help>

**Description**

Makes an RGB image from a 2D image.

-----

**Input**

- A TIFF file

-----

**Output**

- An RGB image in PNG format.

-----

**Example**

If we use the TIFF file generated by running demo2D00, then we can generate the
following RGB image by selecting the indices (R,G,B)=(1,2,3)

.. image:: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/icaoberg/cellorganizer-galaxy-tools/dev/tools/cellorganizer/images/show_RGB_image.png
  :height: 250
  :target: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/icaoberg/cellorganizer-galaxy-tools/dev/tools/cellorganizer/images/show_RGB_image.png
</help>
</tool>
